(5845, 332, 5844, 'Abbas', 1, '', 1235916364, 'No, it not possible for any bullet to fire by itself. \n\nWell made bullets have a very long life if stored properly. People routinely buy surplus army ammo from their governments worldwide at concessional rates. \n\nI myself have fired 40-50 year old bullets without any issues. I also had a box of 25 British made Elly which were about 30 years old and all fired perfectly. Still have about 10 or 15 of them somewhere.\n\nAbout WAH/Shaheen/local bullets the word is that use them within 2-3 years, but I find that to be part of the ''local made things are substandard'' paranoia. I have several 20-25 year old Shaheen cartridges and I''m almost 90 % sure they will fire as I tested several from the box and they worked fine. Messy though because at that time they used to make the shell from cardboard or something like that and it dries over time.\n\nFor sport all ammo is great, for SD/HD try to keep as fresh ammo as possible.\n\nBtw for people like me that like to buy most of their ammo in one go and use it over time. The best thing to store it in is sawdust and sealed airtight with plastic.', 0, 1, '203.81.194.221', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 438, 7165),
