(7956, 418, 7942, 'Connector', 122, '', 1237377279, '[quote=Nabeel][url]http://books.google.com.pk/books?id=1lRy3Y6ZtU4C&pg=PA568&lpg=PA568&dq=M20,M213(9mm)&source=bl&ots=7kRlo2tj9u&sig=dMsrMQaqBpHWVwgRP8vMZiGBvbg&hl=en&ei=67DASevhJ9LEkAWH8_gu&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=1&ct=result#PPP1,M1[/url][/quote]\nNabeel this link is a good reference.Just for the info of all Glock owners.If  you dissassemble\nthe  striker from the firing pin spacer sleeve make sure while assembling it back the spring cups are placed at 90 degrees to the end of coil of the spring.Since the spring cups are two halves if not placed in this manner they are likely to get unseated.', 0, 1, '116.71.10.14', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 548, 9702),
(7957, 412, 7788, 'Zubair', 100, '', 1237377695, '7.62*25mm is a high velocity + high pressure round. Its more devastating then 9*19mm. But at the same time its high recoil effects its accuracy.The reason it has been abandoned is because it is known to cross through most human targets & hit others as well. A friend of mine ,a doctor & a gun enthusiast, says the worst bullet wounds he has seen were by 7.62*25mm. Anyway I would love to see some Rifle or Carbine in the same.', 0, 1, '203.128.13.208', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 538, 9703),
