(9530, 260, 4284, 'Kulachi', 127, '', 1238140934, 'Hedging means you never entered the market. It not only kills your loss, it also kills your profit. Hedging is only used for two major things: 1. Derivatives & futures/forward contracts (when you want to hedge your delta/gamma/theta) or 2. Risk Management (when you want to reduce your overall risk as an institution). If a trader says he hedges, he is saying that "I fire blanks" :-)\n\nAlso note that hedging is always "very calculated". Mostly, the order originates from a regression analysis in an excel sheet (in case of some simple oil/commodities hedging) or from a complicated computer model (mostly in case of derivatives). Therefore, these orders are "not trader-discretionary"; rather they are automated.', 0, 1, '124.29.244.50', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 343, 11528),
