(15052, 650, 0, 'Enigmatic Desires', 430, '', 1240097638, 'When people go for different calibres for self defense. They usually go for the size and weight of a projectile...\n\nThe third equally important (though usually overlooked) part of the trinity is the ''velocity'' of the bullet. \n\nThe ''effectiveness'' of any bullet is usually gauged by the OSS (One shot stop) factor. i.e the assailant stops doing whatever he is doing and/or if he is running. he wont get beyond10-12 feet after being shot once.\n\nBased on NYPD shootings of the past few decades. (As par a research conducted in 1999) the .357''s legendary stopping power (around 93%)was eclipsed by the .40 S&W.  \n\nSpecifically hornady JHP +P (high velocity) ammo. A whopping 97% OSS! \n\nEven though in size and weight this largely overlooked calibre is positively diminutive in comparison.', 0, 1, '119.73.68.87', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 924, 18486),
